commit.message: moved network closing prompt before displaying the web crawler dialog
commented out dbg messages in edge creation, they were slowing down the app
work on #140 -- mostly done, needs to fix/update inDegree after filtering edges by their weight
removed setDisabledEdgesByWeight() -- the latter was moved to Graph (so that we can notify target vertices that their inbound links have been disabled

added GraphVertex::setInEdgeEnabled and GraphVertex::setInEdgeWeight -- removed setDisabledEdgesByWeight() -- the latter was moved to Graph (so that we can notify target vertices that their inbound links have been disabled
new graph api function to enable/disable in/outedges by their numbers
do not continue in Matrix::solve() when no memory can be allocated
removed some debug msgs from KW algorithm -- added a check if the linear system could not be solved due to memory no allocation
fixed another regression when destroying a node
fixed regression in close file dialog, ESC or cancel must abort the current action and let the current net intact

fixed another regression, this time not updating the canvas width and height in Graph (because the resize event and signal from GW was sent BEFORE we had actually connected the signal/slot mechanisms)
fixed regression in computing prominence distribution and updating the minichart after applying a prominence layout
replaced deprecated foreach with for ranged, code cleanup, disabled debug messages in graphics node and edges
